Kym D. made a new post @20 Nov (2023-11-20 06:20:10)
Hi everyone ... Welcome to freelancer ... I am also one of the new moderators. I have worked through freelancer for 15 years. My advice for the day is to start by reading the site's terms and conditions ... this is incredibly important as it will tell you how the site works, and what you can and cannot do here ... https://www.freelancer.com.au/about/terms?w=f&ngsw-bypass= It is also important to read the site's message about scammers on every job you bid on. This way you will avoid doing work for nothing. And do not communicate offsite because if a client asks you to communicate offsite, it is usually a scammer.Have a great day ...
